        "headline": "Flood Warning issued June 7 at 8:17PM CDT until June 8 at 2:32PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK",
        "description": "...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in\nOklahoma...\n\nPoteau River near Panama affecting Le Flore County.\n\n* WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast.\n\n* WHERE...Poteau River near Panama.\n\n* WHEN...Until early Monday afternoon.\n\n* IMPACTS...At 31.0 feet, minor agricultural flooding occurs.\nWilliams Road east of Panama is flooded.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...\n- At 7:30 PM CDT Sunday the stage was 30.9 feet.\n- Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 31.7\nfeet just after midnight tonight. It will then fall below\nflood stage Monday morning.\n- Flood stage is 29.0 feet.\n- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood",
